{"type":"message","id":"48150201","parentId":"fe7368e7","timestamp":"2026-03-23T19:18:53.464Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_e9wp7q49qts9_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 150841\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: research/TIC-CLASSIFIER.md (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze my current state and determine the best single action to advance my goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at my goals, the most immediate and concrete next action is the TIC Experiment mentioned in Phase 1 Advancement:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThis is the \"NEXT ACTION\" specified. I should implement a basic TIC classifier to test the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis.\r\n\r\nLet me check what files I have available:\r\n- `logs/pulse_*.md` files exist (mentioned in recent: pulse_2026-03-23 145928.md)\r\n- `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md` should exist (just created this session according to goals)\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action would be to:\r\n1. Create a TIC experiment script that analyzes the pulse logs\r\n2. This tests the hypothesis that causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nLet me create a simple PowerShell or Python script that:\r\n- Reads recent pulse logs\r\n- Extracts \"invariant\" elements (things that persist across pulses)\r\n- Extracts \"variant\" elements (things that change)\r\n- Attempts to classify them\r\n- Attempts to predict next pulse from invariants\r\n\r\nThis directly tests the key insight and advances Phase 1.\r\n\r\nI'll create a PowerShell script since Breakaway uses PowerShell (pulse.ps1 exists).\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC Experiment is the most immediate next action to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to analyze existing pulse logs to test if invariant structure can predict future pulses and classify content as invariant vs. variant.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `tic_experiment.ps1` - a PowerShell script that analyzes pulse logs to test the hypothesis that causal structure IS invariant structure. The script will extract invariants (persistent elements across pulses) and variants (changing elements), classify them, and attempt next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Experiment - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n# Tests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$PulseCount = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogPattern = \"logs/pulse_*.md\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# --- Phase 1: Load pulse logs ---\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Experiment ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"Loading last $PulseCount pulse logs...\"\r\n\r\n$pulseLogs = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogPattern | \r\n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \r\n    Select-Object -First $PulseCount\r\n\r\nif ($pulseLogs.Count -lt 5) {\r\n    Write-Warning \"Insufficient pulse logs found. Need at least 5.\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Loaded $($pulseLogs.Count) pulse logs\"\r\n\r\n# --- Phase 2: Parse pulse content into structured segments ---\r\nWrite-Host \"`nParsing pulse content...\"\r\n\r\n$pulses = @()\r\nforeach ($log in $pulseLogs) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $log.FullName -Raw\r\n    $pulses += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        File     = $log.Name\r\n        Content  = $content\r\n        Lines    = ($content -split \"`n\").Trim() | Where-Object { $_ -ne \"\" }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# --- Phase 3: Extract candidate invariants and variants ---\r\nWrite-Host \"Extracting invariant/variant candidates...\"\r\n\r\n$allSegments = @{}\r\nforeach ($pulse in $pulses) {\r\n    foreach ($line in $pulse.Lines) {\r\n        if (-not $allSegments.ContainsKey($line)) {\r\n            $allSegments[$line] = [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n                Text     = $line\r\n                Count    = 0\r\n                PulseIds = @()\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        $allSegments[$line].Count++\r\n        $allSegments[$line].PulseIds += $pulse.File\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# --- Phase 4: Classify as Invariant (present in >80% of pulses) or Variant ---\r\n$threshold = [math]::Ceiling($pulses.Count * 0.8)\r\n$invariants = @()\r\n$variants = @()\r\n\r\nforeach ($seg in $allSegments.Values) {\r\n    if ($seg.Count -ge $threshold) {\r\n        $invariants += $seg\r\n    } else {\r\n        $variants += $seg\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Classification results:\"\r\nWrite-Host \"  Invariants (>$threshold pulses): $($invariants.Count)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"  Variants (<$threshold pulses): $($variants.Count)\"\r\n\r\n# --- Phase 5: Next-pulse prediction from invariants ---\r\nWrite-Host \"`n--- Next-Pulse Prediction Test ---\"\r\n\r\n# Use last N-1 pulses to predict the last pulse\r\n$trainingPulses = $pulses[0..($pulses.Count - 2)]\r\n$testPulse = $pulses[-1]\r\n\r\n$predictedContent = $invariants | Where-Object { \r\n    $_.Count -ge [math]::Ceiling($trainingPulses.Count * 0.8) \r\n} | Select-Object -ExpandProperty Text\r\n\r\n$actualContent = $testPulse.Lines\r\n\r\n# Calculate overlap\r\n$overlap = ($predictedContent | Where-Object { $_ -in $actualContent }).Count\r\n$totalPredicted = $predictedContent.Count\r\n$totalActual = $actualContent.Count\r\n\r\n$precision = if ($totalPredicted -gt 0) { $overlap / $totalPredicted } else { 0 }\r\n$recall = if ($totalActual -gt 0) { $overlap / $total\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 15:09:02"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":559,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 150841\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: